This data was collected (*********) through an interactive on-line personality test.
The personality test was constructed with the "Big-Five Factor Markers" from the IPIP. ********************************************
************ were informed that their responses would be recorded and used for research at the beginning of the test, and asked to confirm their consent at the end of the test.

The following items were presented on one page and each was rated on a five point scale using radio buttons. The order on page was was EXT1, AGR1, CSN1, EST1, OPN1, EXT2, etc.
The scale was labeled 1=Disagree, 3=Neutral, 5=Agree

EXT1 I am the life of the party.
EXT2 I don't talk a lot.
EXT3 I feel comfortable around ******.
EXT4 I keep in the background.
EXT5 I start conversations.
EXT6 I have little to say.
EXT7 I talk to a lot of different ****** at parties.
EXT8 I don't like to draw attention to myself.
EXT9 I don't mind being the center of attention.
EXT10 I am quiet around *********.
EST1 I get stressed out easily.
EST2 I am relaxed most of the time.
EST3 I worry about things.
EST4 I seldom feel blue.
EST5 I am easily disturbed.
EST6 I get upset easily.
EST7 I change my mood a lot.
EST8 I have frequent mood swings.
EST9 I get irritated easily.
EST10 I often feel blue.
AGR1 I feel little concern for others.
AGR2 I am interested in ******.
AGR3 I insult ******.
**** I sympathize with others' feelings.
**** I am not interested in other ******'s problems.
**** I have a soft heart.
**** I am not really interested in others.
AGR8 I take time out for others.
AGR9 I feel others' emotions.
AGR10 I make people feel at ease.
CSN1 I am always prepared.
CSN2 I leave my belongings around.
CSN3 I pay attention to details.
CSN4 I make a mess of things.
CSN5 I get chores done right away.
CSN6 I often forget to put things back in their proper place.
CSN7 I like order.
CSN8 I shirk my duties.
CSN9 I follow a schedule.
CSN10 I am exacting in my work.
**** I have a rich vocabulary.
OPN2 I have difficulty understanding abstract ideas.
OPN3 I have a vivid imagination.
OPN4 I am not interested in abstract ideas.
OPN5 I have excellent ideas.
OPN6 I do not have a good imagination.
OPN7 I am quick to understand things.
OPN8 I use difficult words.
OPN9 I spend time reflecting on things.
OPN10 I am full of ideas.

The time spent on each question is also recorded in milliseconds. These are the variables ending in _E. This was calculated by taking the time when the button for the question was clicked minus the time of the most recent other button click.

dateload The timestamp when the survey was started.
screenw The width the of ****'s screen in pixels
screenh The height of the ****'s screen in pixels
introelapse The time in seconds spent on the landing / intro page
testelapse The time in seconds spent on the page with the survey questions
endelapse The time in seconds spent on the finalization page (where the **** was asked to indicate if they has answered accurately and their answers could be stored and used for research. Again: this dataset only includes ***** who answered "Yes" to this question, ***** were free to answer no and could still view their results either way)
IPC The number of records from the ****'s IP address in the dataset. For max cleanliness, only use records where this value is 1. High values can be because of shared networks (e.g. entire universities) or multiple submissions
country The country, determined by technical information (NOT ASKED AS A QUESTION)
lat_appx_lots_of_err approximate latitude of ****. determined by technical information, THIS IS NOT VERY ACCURATE. Read the article "How an internet mapping glitch turned a random Kansas farm into a digital hell" ******************************************************************************************* to learn about the perils of relying on this information
long_appx_lots_of_err approximate longitude of ****
